[Thanks to Bob Scott for this informative up-date. Strange that 100% of
encephalitis cases have been diagnosed. In this country and in other
western countries a far lower percentage of encephalitis cases ever have an
etiologic agent associated with them. Herpes, enteroviruses, and other
agents likely are the cause of the undiagnosed illnesses but definitive
diagnosis never equals 100%. I wonder whether some other (inapparent to
me) screening process is being used. - Mod.CHC
......................................chc/es
--
